name: Утилиты для работы с ORACLE: Quest SQL Navigator v.6.2 [СУБД]
author: yurmala
description:
Утилиты для работы с ORACLE: Quest SQL Navigator v.6.2Год выпуска: 2009
Версия: 6.2.0.1500
Разработчик: Quest Software
Платформа: win32
Совместимость с Vista: да
Системные требования: System Requirements
Язык интерфейса: только английский
Таблэтка: ПрисутствуетОписание: Довольно удобная среда для разработки PL/SQL пакетов и работы с SQL под OracleЧто нового в этой версии:New Features in SQL Navigator® 6.2.0 * Enhancements on the Project Manager including a preference to hide Project Manager after connecting.
* New Search feature for the Preferences window.
* Preference to format after extracting the ddl.
* Import/Export tables.
* New layout for the Oracle Logon window.
* Session browser to support RAC database.
* Revised layout to accommodate multiple code editor windows.
* Code Editor - Bug fixes and enhancements.
* Other General bug fixes and enhancements.

Системные требования
Minimum Hardware Requirements * Pentium 3 600MHz
* 512MB RAM/1GB*
* CD-ROM Drive (for CD based installs)
* XGA (1024x768) or better monitor
* DirectDraw 7 capable graphics adapterNB: 110MB disk space required for Xpert installation, less for Standard & Professional Editions.
* 1GB RAM recommended for running SQL Tuning in Xpert EditionSoftware RequirementsClient configuration * Microsoft Windows 2000 (SP4) Workstation and Server versions
* Microsoft Windows XP Pro with the latest Service Pack
* Microsoft Windows XP Pro x64 Edition with the latest Service Pack
* Windows Vista Business (32 bit) (Compliant - Install and Run as Administrator) - Oracle client for Microsoft Windows Vista will be required. Please refer to http://www.oracle.com/technology/software/products/database/oracle10g/htdocs/10203vista.html
* Microsoft Windows Server 2003 with the latest Service Pack.
* Oracle client 8i, 9i, 10g and 11gServer configurationSQL Navigator supports Oracle versions 8.1.7 through 11g. However it is recommended that you connect to Oracle 9i databases via Oracle client 9i and above.
Please refer to the Oracle documentation for 10g instant client server compatibility.
